addRecentlyFoundChat.desc:
Adds a chat to the list of recently found chats. The chat is added to the beginning of the list. If the chat is already in the list, it will be removed from the list first.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: Chat identifier.

fields.name: user_ids
fields.desc: Identifiers of the users to be added to the chat.

addChatMembers.desc:
Adds multiple new members to a chat. Currently this option is only available for supergroups and channels. This option can't be used to join a chat. Members can't be added to a channel if it has more than 200 members. Members will not be added until the chat state has been synchronized with the server.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: call_id

fields.name: protocol

acceptCall.desc:
Accepts an incoming call.

fields.name: sticker

addRecentSticker.desc:
Manually adds a new sticker to the list of recently used stickers. The new sticker is added to the top of the list. If the sticker was already in the list, it is removed from the list first. Only stickers belonging to a sticker set can be added to this list.

addChatMember.desc:

Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

answerCallbackQuery.desc:

Stops the downloading of a file. If a file has already been downloaded, does nothing.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: entry
fields.desc: The network statistics entry with the data to be added to statistics.

addNetworkStatistics.desc:
Adds the specified data to data usage statistics. Can be called before authorization.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: animation
fields.desc: The animation file to be added. Only animations known to the server (i.e. successfully sent via a message) can be added to the list.

addSavedAnimation.desc:
Manually adds a new animation to the list of saved animations. The new animation is added to the beginning of the list. If the animation was already in the list, it is removed first. Only non-secret video animations with MIME type "video/mp4" can be added to the list.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: user_id
fields.desc: User identifier.

blockUser.desc:
Adds a user to the blacklist.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: shipping_query_id
fields.desc: Identifier of the shipping query.

fields.name: shipping_options
fields.desc: Available shipping options.

fields.name: error_message
fields.desc: An error message, empty on success.

answerShippingQuery.desc:
Sets the result of a shipping query; for bots only.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: custom_query_id
fields.desc: Identifier of a custom query.

fields.name: data
fields.desc: JSON-serialized answer to the query.

answerCustomQuery.desc:
Answers a custom query; for bots only.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: token
fields.desc: The bot token.

checkAuthenticationBotToken.desc:
Checks the authentication token of a bot; to log in as a bot. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitPhoneNumber. Can be used instead of setAuthenticationPhoneNumber and checkAuthenticationCode to log in.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: pre_checkout_query_id
fields.desc: Identifier of the pre-checkout query.

fields.name: error_message
fields.desc: An error message, empty on success.

answerPreCheckoutQuery.desc:
Sets the result of a pre-checkout query; for bots only.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: set_id
fields.desc: Identifier of the sticker set.

fields.name: is_installed
fields.desc: The new value of is_installed.

fields.name: is_archived
fields.desc: The new value of is_archived. A sticker set can't be installed and archived simultaneously.

changeStickerSet.desc:
Installs/uninstalls or activates/archives a sticker set.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: code
fields.desc: Verification code received by SMS, phone call or flash call.

checkChangePhoneNumberCode.desc:
Checks the authentication code sent to confirm a new phone number of the user.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: invite_link
fields.desc: Invite link to be checked; should begin with "https://t.me/joinchat/", "https://telegram.me/joinchat/", or "https://telegram.dog/joinchat/".

checkChatInviteLink.desc:
Checks the validity of an invite link for a chat and returns information about the corresponding chat.
Returns object_ptr<ChatInviteLinkInfo>.

fields.name: contacts
fields.desc: The new list of contacts.

changeImportedContacts.desc:
Changes imported contacts using the list of current user contacts saved on the device. Imports newly added contacts and, if at least the file database is enabled, deletes recently deleted contacts. Query result depends on the result of the previous query, so only one query is possible at the same time.
Returns object_ptr<ImportedContacts>.

clearImportedContacts.desc:
Clears all imported contacts.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: encryption_key
fields.desc: Encryption key to check or set up.

checkDatabaseEncryptionKey.desc:
Checks the database encryption key for correctness. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitEncryptionKey.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

clearRecentlyFoundChats.desc:
Clears the list of recently found chats.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: is_attached
fields.desc: Pass true to clear the list of stickers recently attached to photo or video files; pass false to clear the list of recently sent stickers.

clearRecentStickers.desc:
Clears the list of recently used stickers.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: phone_number
fields.desc: The new phone number of the user in international format.

fields.name: allow_flash_call
fields.desc: Pass true if the code can be sent via flash call to the specified phone number.

fields.name: is_current_phone_number
fields.desc: Pass true if the phone number is used on the current device. Ignored if allow_flash_call is false.

changePhoneNumber.desc:
Changes the phone number of the user and sends an authentication code to the user's new phone number. On success, returns information about the sent code.
Returns object_ptr<AuthenticationCodeInfo>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: Chat identifier.

closeChat.desc:
This method should be called if the chat is closed by the user. Many useful activities depend on the chat being opened or closed.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

close.desc:
Closes the TDLib instance. All databases will be flushed to disk and properly closed. After the close completes, updateAuthorizationState with authorizationStateClosed will be sent.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: secret_chat_id

closeSecretChat.desc:
Closes a secret chat, effectively transfering its state to secretChatStateClosed.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

createNewBasicGroupChat.desc:

fields.name: user_id

createNewSecretChat.desc:
Creates a new secret chat. Returns the newly created chat.
Returns object_ptr<Chat>.

fields.name: file_id
fields.desc: Identifier of the file to stop uploading.

cancelUploadFile.desc:
Stops the uploading of a file. Supported only for files uploaded by using uploadFile. For other files the behavior is undefined.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: code
fields.desc: The verification code received via SMS, Telegram message, phone call, or flash call.

fields.name: first_name

fields.name: last_name
fields.desc: If the user is not yet registered; the last name of the user; optional; 0-255 characters.

checkAuthenticationCode.desc:
Checks the authentication code. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitCode.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: is_masks

createNewStickerSet.desc:

fields.name: is_channel

fields.name: reason
fields.desc: The reason why the account was deleted; optional.

deleteAccount.desc:
Deletes the account of the current user, deleting all information associated with the user from the server. The phone number of the account can be used to create a new account.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: password
fields.desc: The password to check.

checkAuthenticationPassword.desc:
Checks the authentication password for correctness. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitPassword.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Chat identifier.

fields.name: remove_from_chat_list
fields.desc: Pass true if the chat should be removed from the chats list.

deleteChatHistory.desc:
Deletes all messages in the chat only for the user. Cannot be used in channels and public supergroups.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: user_id
fields.desc: User identifier.

deleteChatMessagesFromUser.desc:
Deletes all messages sent by the specified user to a chat. Supported only in supergroups; requires can_delete_messages administrator privileges.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: Chat identifier.

fields.name: message_id
fields.desc: The message identifier of the used keyboard.

deleteChatReplyMarkup.desc:
Deletes the default reply markup from a chat. Must be called after a one-time keyboard or a ForceReply reply markup has been used. UpdateChatReplyMarkup will be sent if the reply markup will be changed.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: file_id
fields.desc: Identifier of the file to delete.

deleteFile.desc:
Deletes a file from the TDLib file cache.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Chat identifier.

fields.desc: Identifiers of the messages to be deleted.

fields.name: revoke
fields.desc: Pass true to try to delete outgoing messages for all chat members (may fail if messages are too old). Always true for supergroups, channels and secret chats.

fields.name: profile_photo_id
fields.desc: Identifier of the profile photo to delete.

deleteProfilePhoto.desc:
Deletes a profile photo. If something changes, updateUser will be sent.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

deleteSavedCredentials.desc:
Deletes saved credentials for all payment provider bots.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

deleteSavedOrderInfo.desc:
Deletes saved order info.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: supergroup_id
fields.desc: Identifier of the supergroup or channel.

deleteSupergroup.desc:
Deletes a supergroup or channel along with all messages in the corresponding chat. This will release the supergroup or channel username and remove all members; requires creator privileges in the supergroup or channel. Chats with more than 1000 members can't be deleted using this method.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

destroy.desc:
Closes the TDLib instance, destroying all local data without a proper logout. The current user session will remain in the list of all active sessions. All local data will be destroyed. After the destruction completes updateAuthorizationState with authorizationStateClosed will be sent.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

editMessageText.desc:

fields.name: chat_id

fields.desc: Identifiers of the messages to forward.

fields.name: from_background
fields.desc: Pass true if the message is sent from the background.

fields.desc: True, if the messages should be grouped into an album after forwarding. For this to work, no more than 10 messages may be forwarded, and all of them must be photo or video messages.

forwardMessages.desc:
Forwards previously sent messages. Returns the forwarded messages in the same order as the message identifiers passed in message_ids. If a message can't be forwarded, null will be returned instead of the message.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: Chat identifier.

generateChatInviteLink.desc:
Generates a new invite link for a chat; the previously generated link is revoked. Available for basic groups, supergroups, and channels. In basic groups this can be called only by the group's creator; in supergroups and channels this requires appropriate administrator rights.
Returns object_ptr<ChatInviteLink>.

fields.name: password
fields.desc: Persistent user password.

fields.name: valid_for
fields.desc: Time during which the temporary password will be valid, in seconds; should be between 60 and 86400.

createTemporaryPassword.desc:
Creates a new temporary password for processing payments.
Returns object_ptr<TemporaryPasswordState>.

fields.desc: Chat identifier.

fields.name: is_spam_chat
fields.desc: If true, the chat will be reported as spam; otherwise it will be marked as not spam.

changeChatReportSpamState.desc:
Used to let the server know whether a chat is spam or not. Can be used only if ChatReportSpamState.can_report_spam is true. After this request, ChatReportSpamState.can_report_spam becomes false forever.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

editMessageLiveLocation.desc:
Edits the message content of a live location. Messages can be edited for a limited period of time specified in the live location. Returns the edited message after the edit is completed server-side.
Returns object_ptr<Message>.

fields.name: generation_id
fields.desc: The identifier of the generation process.

fields.name: error
fields.desc: If set, means that file generation has failed and should be terminated.

finishFileGeneration.desc:
Finishes the file generation.

getActiveSessions.desc:
Returns all active sessions of the current user.
Returns object_ptr<Sessions>.

fields.desc: Identifier of the sticker set from which to return the result.

getArchivedStickerSets.desc:

Returns all active live locations that should be updated by the client. The list is persistent across application restarts only if the message database is used.

Returns the period of inactivity after which the account of the current user will automatically be deleted.
Returns object_ptr<AccountTtl>.

Returns the current authorization state; this is an offline request. For informational purposes only. Use updateAuthorizationState instead to maintain the current authorization state.
Returns object_ptr<AuthorizationState>.

getAttachedStickerSets.desc:
Returns a list of sticker sets attached to a file. Currently only photos and videos can have attached sticker sets.

getBasicGroupFullInfo.desc:

getBlockedUsers.desc:

fields.desc: Identifier of the message starting from which history must be fetched; use 0 to get results from the beginning (i.e., from oldest to newest).

fields.desc: Specify 0 to get results from exactly the from_message_id or a negative offset to get the specified message and some newer messages.

fields.desc: The maximum number of messages to be returned; must be positive and can't be greater than 100. If the offset is negative, the limit must be greater than -offset. Fewer messages may be returned than specified by the limit, even if the end of the message history has not been reached.

fields.name: only_local
fields.desc: If true, returns only messages that are available locally without sending network requests.
